        <div class="cover-image flat d-flex justify-content-center flex-column"><div data-is-viewable="" class="cover-image__image"><a href="/toc/radiographics/27/6" title="Go to RadioGraphics " class="d-block"><img src="/cms/10.1148/radiographics.2007.27.issue-6/asset/14a16858-7514-1685-f751-a16858f7514a/radiographics.2007.27.issue-6.cover.gif" alt="Go to RadioGraphics " loading="lazy"/></a></div></div>
<div class="core-journal-description"><div property="isPartOf" typeof="Periodical"><span property="name">RadioGraphics</span></div><div class="core-enumeration"><span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationVolume">Volume <span property="volumeNumber">27</span></span> • <span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationIssue">Number <span property="issueNumber">6</span></span> • <span property="datePublished">Nov 1 2007</span></div><div class="core-pagination"><span class="heading">Pages</span>: <span class="content"><span property="pageStart">1595</span> - <span property="pageEnd">1610</span></span></div><div class="core-pmid"><span class="heading">PubMed</span>: <a class="content" href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/18025505/" property="sameAs" target="_blank" title="Link to PubMed">18025505</a></div></div></div></section><section class="core-copyright"><h4>Copyright</h4><div role="paragraph">© RSNA, 2007.</div></section><section class="core-history"><h4>History</h4><div><b class="core-label">Published online</b>: Nov 1 2007</div></section><section class="core-permissions"><h4>Permissions</h4><div>Request permissions for this article.</div><div><a class="btn" href="https://marketplace.copyright.com/rs-ui-web/mp/search/all/10.1148%2Frg.276065002">Request Permissions</a></div></section><section property="keywords"><h4>Keyword</h4><ol><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=IVC+%3D+inferior+vena+cava&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">IVC = inferior vena cava</a></li></ol></section><section class="core-article-notes"><h4>Notes</h4><div role="paragraph">Cardiac tamponade is a life-threatening condition, and awareness of its imaging findings in the proper clinical setting may lead to early diagnosis and prompt lifesaving interventions; the pathophysiologic, clinical, and imaging features of this condition are discussed with an emphasis on the CT findings.</div></section></section><section id="tab-contributors" role="t